---
title: Quick Start
description: Get productive with {{TOOL_NAME}} in 60 seconds
---

## Show help

```bash
{{TOOL_NAME}} --help
```

## Check version

```bash
{{TOOL_NAME}} version
```

## JSON output

Every command supports `--json` for scripting:

```bash
{{TOOL_NAME}} <subcommand> --json | jq '.'
```

## Dry run

Preview changes before applying them:

```bash
{{TOOL_NAME}} <subcommand> --dry-run
```

## Shell completions

```bash
# bash
{{TOOL_NAME}} completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/{{TOOL_NAME}}

# zsh
{{TOOL_NAME}} completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_{{TOOL_NAME}}"

# fish
{{TOOL_NAME}} completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/{{TOOL_NAME}}.fish
```
